The energy consumption per capita is very different for different countries, e.g. it is 9.9 kW/person in the US, 5.5 kW/person in Germany, and 0.9 kW/person in Africa. The world average is 18,000GW/7.3billionpeople=2.5kW\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
